                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8508: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-31T00:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1927—midnight</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received April 1—6:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>311. Following telegram has been sent to the commander in chief, United States
                    Asiatic Fleet: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 31, 11 p.m. Reference my number 277, March 29, noon, to the
                            Department of State, repeated to the American consul general at Shanghai
                            for your information.</p>
                        <p>1. As a result of conference this afternoon with Brigadier General
                            Castner and the American consul in charge at Tientsin, I recommend the
                            despatch <hi rend="italic">Sacramento</hi> or <hi rend="italic"
                                >Asheville</hi> to Tientsin for an indefinite stay. This seems
                            necessary in view of the general situation, which appears to be growing
                            more dangerous, particularly at Tientsin where Communist agitators are
                            reliably reported to have concentrated for the purpose of inciting
                            immediate antiforeign feeling and disorders.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
